<!-- Moved from templates/posts/default.php -->

    <div><p><a title="Platforms > Nintendo [23,696 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo">Nintendo</a> will host a Nintendo Direct broadcast on <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20260609T1400" target="_blank" rel="noopener">June 9 at 7:00 a.m PT / 10:00 a.m. ET</a>, featuring approximately 50 minutes of updates, followed directly by a Nintendo Treehouse: Live! that will run for approximately 95 minutes, the company <a href="https://twitter.com/NintendoAmerica/status/2063984598275490250" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announced</a>. You will be able to watch it on YouTube (<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PvUPDSDZg1k" target="_blank" rel="noopener">America</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cCI0FJniEok" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Europe</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AxKtVcMNpzY" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Japan</a>) and Nintendo.com (<a href="https://www.nintendo.com/us/nintendo-direct/06-09-2026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">America</a>, <a href="https://www.nintendo.co.uk/News/Nintendo-Direct/Latest-Nintendo-Direct/Nintendo-Direct-698557.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Europe</a>, <a href="https://www.nintendo.com/jp/nintendo-direct/20260609/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Japan</a>). <span id="more-1057000"></span></p><p>Stay tuned.</p></div>

        
    
